  • public class VideoExport
extends Object
    +Example
    import com.hamoid.*;

VideoExport videoExport;

void setup() {
  size(600, 600);
  
  videoExport = new VideoExport(this, "basic.mp4");
}
void draw() {
  background(#224488);
  rect(frameCount * frameCount % width, 0, 40, height);

  videoExport.saveFrame();
}

      • VideoExport

        public VideoExport(PApplet parent,
           String outputFileName,
           PGraphics pg)
        Constructor that allows to set a PGraphics to export as video (advanced)
        Parameters:
        parent - Parent PApplet, normally "this" when called from setup()
        outputFileName - The name of the video file to produce, for instance "beauty.mp4"
        pg - PGraphics object to export as video
        +Example
        import com.hamoid.*;

VideoExport videoExport;
PGraphics pg;

void setup() {
  size(600, 600);
  pg = createGraphics(640, 480);
  
  videoExport = new VideoExport(this, "pgraphics.mp4", pg);
}
void draw() {
  background(0);
  text("exporting video " + frameCount, 50, 50);
  
  pg.beginDraw();
  pg.background(#224488);
  pg.rect(pg.width * noise(frameCount * 0.01), 0, 40, pg.height);
  pg.endDraw();

  videoExport.saveFrame();
}

    • Method Detail

      • setGraphics

        public void setGraphics(PGraphics pg)
        Set the PGraphics element. Advanced use only. Optional.
        Parameters:
        pg - A PGraphics object. Probably only called when working with an array of PGraphics objects.

      • setQuality

        public void setQuality(int crf)
        Set the quality of the produced video file. Optional.
        Parameters:
        crf - A value between 0 (high compression) and 100 (high quality, lossless). Default is 70.

      • setFrameRate

        public void setFrameRate(float frameRate)
        Set the frame rate of the produced video file. Optional.
        Parameters:
        frameRate - The frame rate at which the resulting video file should be played. The default is 30, which is the recommended for online video.

      • dontCallLoadPixels

        public void dontCallLoadPixels()
        Tells VideoExport not to call loadPixels(). Use it only if you already call loadPixels() in your program. Useful to avoid calling it twice, which might hurt the performance a bit. Optional.

      • saveFrame

        public void saveFrame()
        Adds one frame to the video file. The frame will be the content of the display, or the content of a PGraphics if you specified one in the constructor.

      • forgetFfmpegPath

        public void forgetFfmpegPath()
        Makes the library forget about where the ffmpeg binary was located. Useful if you moved ffmpeg to a different location. After calling this function the library will ask you again for the location of ffmpeg. Optional.

      • dispose

        public void dispose()
        Called automatically by Processing to clean up before shut down

      • version

        Return the version of the library.

        String

        Called internally by the file selector when the user chooses the location of ffmpeg on the disk.

        selection -
